[[Get List of GPG Keys]] first to get the key details. you can use both your key id or email address directly in the following command to get the public key. I choose email since it is more straightforward

``` {.bash org-language="sh" results="output drawer"}
gpg --armor --export kuzey.koc@kartaca.com
```

